There are 4 types of access Modifiers as public private protected and default

Public -> Something need to accessed outside its package -> make it public. --> Access from anywhere.

For Same packages without public they can be accessed it not pvt
Outside the package they are needed to be the marked public


Private -> Something that should not be able to be accessed outside its class itself, make it public
private variable can only be used in same class

By default -> if any variable / method is neither public nor private then it is a default.
default allows the variable / method to be accessed in same package

Protected -> The protected allow to access the variable/ method to be accessed in the same package AND also outside the package IF another class extends it.
Like Same Package -> OK
different package unrelated Class -> Not ok
Different package related class (Extended base class) ->  OK


----------------------------------------------------------------
So when to use What
----------------------------------------------------------------

In One file there Can only be one public class (No 2 Public classes are allowed)

So try to make your class public, instance variable pvt , methods public

Try Not to keep anything default.

